cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CE 

The paper proposes a market-based framework for resource allocation in edge computing, which involves game theory and optimization techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science). The paper also deals with networking and distributed systems, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper discusses the allocation of resources in a distributed environment, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also mentions fairness properties, which could be related to cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
